Step 1 :- How To Install SSH Server
   -> Command :- sudo apt-get install openssh-server
Step 2 :- Now you need to Enable ssh service
   -> Command :- sudo sysytemctl start ssh
Step 3 :-And Then Test It By Login Into SystemUsing  the given command  
   -> Command :- ssh kali@kali
Step 4 :- First Update And Then Install OpenSSH server.
    -> Command :- sudo apt update
Step 5 :- Now you need to Install OpenSSH Server
    -> Command :- sudo apt install openssh-server
Step 6 :- Now you need to Verify And Run SSh Service
    -> Command :- sudo systemctl status ssh
Step 7 :- Now you to need Configure Firewall And Open Port 22.
     -> Command :- sudo ufw allow ssh
     -> Command :- sudo ufw enable
     -> Command :- sudo ufw status
Step 8 :- To Establish Completed With Own Computer
     -> Command :- ssh 127.0.0.1
Step 9 :- To Check Which User Is Logged In Right Now
     -> Command :- who
